  "texts": [
    "So for X ∈ P ′℘, there is an X ∈ P such that (i) X = ↓(min⟨S, ⊑⟩ ∩ X) = {Y ⊆ min⟨S, ⊑⟩ | ∅ ̸ = Y ⊆ X}.",
    "We claim that h -1 [X] = X.",
    "For the left-to-right inclusion, if x ∈ h -1 [X], so h(x) ∈ X, then by (i), h(x) ⊆ X.",
    "By refinability for X, if x ̸ ∈ X, then there is a minimal point a ⊑ x such that a ̸ ∈ X, so h(x) ̸ ⊆ X, contradicting what we just showed.",
    "Thus, x ∈ X."
  ],
